---
export const prerender = true;
import Shop from '@/layouts/Shop.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '@/components/astro/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { tenant } from '@/config/tenant';

const publishDate = '2026-03-28';
const title = 'LOOP vs Skruf: Which Swedish Brand Is Right for You?';
const description = 'A detailed comparison of LOOP and Skruf nicotine pouches — flavour range, strength, pouch format, and which brand suits different users.';
---

<Shop
  title={`${title} | ${tenant.name}`}
  description={description}
  ogType="article"
>
  <article class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <Breadcrumb items={[
        { label: 'Blog', href: '/blog' },
        { label: 'LOOP vs Skruf' },
      ]} />

      <header class="mb-10">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-primary">Comparison</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">{description}</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <time datetime={publishDate}>March 28, 2026</time>
          <span>&middot;</span>
          <span>8 min read</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&_h2]:text-foreground [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-bold [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:mb-4 [&_h3]:text-foreground [&_h3]:text-xl [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_h3]:mt-8 [&_h3]:mb-3 [&_strong]:text-foreground [&_a]:text-primary [&_a]:underline [&_a:hover]:text-foreground">

        <h2>Two Swedish Brands, Two Different Philosophies</h2>
        <p>
          If you're shopping for nicotine pouches, you've probably seen <a href="/brands/loop">LOOP</a> and
          <a href="/brands/skruf">Skruf</a> everywhere. Both are Swedish, both have strong followings, and both make
          genuinely good products. But they're actually quite different in philosophy. One is the experimental upstart
          chasing wild flavour combinations; the other is the established player focused on refinement and consistency.
        </p>

        <h2>LOOP: The Bold Innovator</h2>
        <p>
          LOOP was launched in 2020 by Another Snus Factory AB (founded 2019) out of Stockholm. Despite being relatively fresh to the
          market, LOOP has carved out a distinct identity through aggressive flavour experimentation and their Instant
          Rush technology — a promise of immediate flavour and nicotine release paired with a lasting hit.
        </p>
        <p>
          The brand went straight for unusual flavour blends you won't find anywhere else: Jalapeno Lime, Habanero Mint,
          Red Chili Melon, Hot Peach, Hot Mango. These aren't typical nicotine pouch offerings. They're the kind of thing
          you try because they sound crazy, then end up ordering regularly because they actually work.
        </p>

        <h3>LOOP's Flavour Range</h3>
        <p>
          LOOP currently offers around 30+ products across several flavour families: spicy lineup (Jalapeno Lime, Red
          Chili Melon, Habanero Mint), traditional mint (Smooth Mint, Cool Mint), fruit-forward (Cassis Bliss, Hot Peach,
          Hot Mango), and unique blends (Licorice Fusion, Creamy Cappuccino, Mint Mania). Nicotine content ranges from
          6.25 mg to 15.5 mg per pouch.
        </p>

        <h2>Skruf: The Established Standard</h2>
        <p>
          Skruf was founded in 2002 by Jonas Engwall and Adam Gillberg. It's now one of Sweden's largest smokeless
          manufacturers and probably the most widely available premium nicotine pouch brand globally. They launched their
          Super White line in 2018 and haven't looked back.
        </p>
        <p>
          Skruf's philosophy is different from LOOP's. Rather than chasing bizarre flavours, Skruf focused on getting
          the fundamentals right: clean materials, consistent quality, and a carefully curated flavour palette. They use
          microcrystalline cellulose (actual plant fibres), high-purity nicotine, and natural flavourings.
        </p>

        <h3>Skruf's Strength Levels</h3>
        <p>
          Skruf uses a numbered system (#2 through #5): <strong>#2 (Light)</strong> at 6 mg per pouch for occasional or
          new users, <strong>#3 (Standard)</strong> at 10 mg for the workhorse strength, <strong>#4 (Extra Strong)</strong>
          at 11 mg for regular users, and <strong>#5 (Ultra Strong)</strong> at 16 mg for experienced users who want a
          serious hit.
        </p>

        <h2>Head-to-Head Comparison</h2>

        <h3>Flavour Range and Variety</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>LOOP wins here, hands down.</strong> If you're the type who gets bored or likes to experiment, LOOP
          gives you permission to try something completely different each time you order. Jalapeno Lime is a genuine
          flavour experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Skruf plays it safer.</strong> Their flavours are all good — genuinely well-executed mint and fruit
          profiles — but they're in the same flavour family as dozens of other brands. The upside is consistency: you
          know exactly what you're getting, and Skruf pulls off "clean mint" better than almost anyone.
        </p>

        <h3>Strength Options and Nicotine Hit</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>LOOP</strong> ranges from 6.25 mg to 15.5 mg. The Instant Rush tech seems to make a difference in
          how quickly the nicotine hits, which some users prefer.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Skruf</strong> has a tidier strength ladder with clear numbering and genuine range from light to
          ultra-strong. If you're new to pouches or <a href="/blog/switching-from-cigarettes-to-nicotine-pouches">switching
          from something stronger</a>, Skruf's #2 and #3 are easier to understand.
        </p>

        <h3>Pouch Format and Feel</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>LOOP</strong> offers slim and mini formats. The pouches are designed for fast saturation and tend to be
          slightly more moist.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Skruf</strong> is famous for its soft, thin pouches. The super slim format (0.7 g) is genuinely discreet
          and comfortable. If discretion and comfort are priority one, Skruf's pouch engineering is slightly ahead.
        </p>

        <h2>Who Should Choose LOOP?</h2>
        <p>
          Pick LOOP if you like variety and don't want to get bored with the same mint flavour repeatedly, you want a
          strong, fast nicotine hit and appreciate the Instant Rush technology, you're willing to experiment with
          boundary-pushing flavour profiles, you care about sustainable packaging (recyclable cans, 50% plant material),
          or you're an experienced user looking for strength options in the 12-15 mg range.
        </p>
        <p>
          In short: LOOP is for the adventurous user who treats pouches like a hobby and enjoys discovery.
        </p>

        <h2>Who Should Choose Skruf?</h2>
        <p>
          Pick Skruf if you know what you want and you want it consistently delivered every time, you prefer classic,
          well-executed flavours — particularly mint, you value comfort and discretion, you're
          <a href="/blog/best-nicotine-pouches-for-beginners-2026">new to nicotine pouches</a> and want an intuitive strength
          system (#2-#5), you want easy global availability, or you prefer a drier pouch feel for extended periods.
        </p>
        <p>
          In short: Skruf is for the user who appreciates quality fundamentals and doesn't need to be surprised.
        </p>

        <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
        <p>
          There's no wrong choice here. LOOP and Skruf represent two valid approaches to the nicotine pouch category.
          LOOP is the innovator breaking expectations with unusual flavours and fast-hit technology. Skruf is the
          reliable professional who's been doing this for years and has refined every detail.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're stuck, buy one can of each. Many serious users actually rotate between them — LOOP for variety,
          Skruf as the default go-to when you just want something straightforward. The Swedish nicotine pouch industry
          is strong enough that both can coexist, and honestly, having choices this good is the real win.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-links -->
      <nav class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-border">
        <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Browse by Flavour</h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <a href="/products/flavor/mint" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Mint</a>
              <a href="/products/flavor/berry" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Berry</a>
              <a href="/products/flavor/citrus" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Citrus</a>
              <a href="/products/flavor/coffee" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Coffee</a>
              <a href="/products/flavor/fruit" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Fruit</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Browse by Strength</h3>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <a href="/products/strength/mild" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Mild</a>
              <a href="/products/strength/regular" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Regular</a>
              <a href="/products/strength/strong" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Strong</a>
              <a href="/products/strength/extra-strong" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Extra Strong</a>
              <a href="/products/strength/super-strong" class="rounded-full bg-muted px-3 py-1.5 text-sm hover:bg-primary/10 transition">Super Strong</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "Article",
        "headline": title,
        "datePublished": publishDate,
        "dateModified": publishDate,
        "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "SnusFriends Editorial" },
        "publisher": {
          "@type": "Organization",
          "name": tenant.name,
          "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": `https://${tenant.domain}/og-image.jpg` }
        },
        "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `https://${tenant.domain}/blog/loop-vs-skruf` },
        "description": description
      })} />
    </div>
  </article>
</Shop>
